This paper deals with a computer vision problem of instance segmentation, which involves identifying and segmenting individual objects within an image. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel segmentation branch, which involves designing a deep learning network, making it relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the speed of the network, which could be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.RO (Robotics).
